<Documentation>
  <Docs DocId="T:SpriteKit.SKPhysicsJoint">
    <summary>Base class for subtypes that join bodies in the physics engine.</summary>
    <remarks>
      <para>Joints must be added to the <see cref="SpriteKit.SKScene" />'s <see cref="SpriteKit.SKScene.PhysicsWorld" /> after the <see cref="SpriteKit.SKPhysicsBody" />s of the <see cref="SpriteKit.SKPhysicsJoint" />. Adding the joint prior to adding the <see cref="SpriteKit.SKPhysicsBody" />s will result in a segfault.</para>
      <para>Subclasses of <see cref="SpriteKit.SKPhysicsJoint" /> have a <c>Create</c> static method that should be used to construct instances.</para>
      <para>
        <img href="~/SpriteKit/_images/SKPhysicsJoint.Hierarchy.png" alt="Class diagram of the SKPhysicsJoint hierarchy" />
      </para>
      <para>
        <list type="table">
          <listheader>
            <term>Class</term>
            <description>Description</description>
          </listheader>
          <item>
            <term>
              <see cref="SpriteKit.SKPhysicsJointFixed" />
            </term>
            <description>Fuses two bodies without allowing movement.</description>
          </item>
          <item>
            <term>
              <see cref="SpriteKit.SKPhysicsJointLimit" />
            </term>
            <description>Limits the maximum distance between two bodies.</description>
          </item>
          <item>
            <term>
              <see cref="SpriteKit.SKPhysicsJointPin" />
            </term>
            <description>Allows two bodies to rotate around an anchor point.</description>
          </item>
          <item>
            <term>
              <see cref="SpriteKit.SKPhysicsJointSliding" />
            </term>
            <description>Allows two bodies to move along an axis.</description>
          </item>
          <item>
            <term>
              <see cref="SpriteKit.SKPhysicsJointSpring" />
            </term>
            <description>Connects two bodies with a spring.</description>
          </item>
        </list>
      </para>
    </remarks>
    <related type="externalDocumentation" href="https://developer.apple.com/library/ios/documentation/SpriteKit/Reference/SKPhysicsJoint_Ref/index.html">Apple documentation for <c>SKPhysicsJoint</c></related>
  </Docs>
</Documentation>